## Steps

### step 1
id: find-account-context-bar
instruction: Go to the Billing Hub (click the Altair logo or "Billing Hub" in the sidebar). Look at the highlighted Account Context Bar below your greeting — it shows the current account name, NPI, and open item count.
success_criteria: You can see the Account Context Bar with the current account displayed.
anchor: "Account Context Bar"
on_success: next
on_stuck: The Account Context Bar is the first card below your greeting on the Billing Hub.

### step 2
id: open-account-switcher
instruction: Click the account name in the Context Bar to open the dropdown. You'll see all accounts with their names and NPI numbers, plus an "All Accounts" option at the top.
success_criteria: The dropdown is open showing all available accounts.
anchor: "account name"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Click directly on the account name text in the Context Bar.

### step 3
id: select-account
instruction: Click the account you want to work in, or click "All Accounts" to see data across all NPIs.
success_criteria: The Context Bar updates to show the selected account. All data across the app — Batches, Payments, Denials, Prior Auths, Patients — now filters to that account.
anchor: "account option"
on_success: completion
on_stuck: Click the account name from the dropdown list.

## Completion Message
account switched. every screen in altair now shows data for that NPI only. switch back to "All Accounts" anytime from the same Context Bar.

